other_tests.findings: Normal sinus rhythm at a rate of 91, with inverted T waves in leads V1 and V2, and low upright T waves in lead V.
An intraluminal mass occluding the left pulmonary artery and involving the main and proximal right pulmonary arteries.
Myxoid spindle-cell tumor, with occasional mitotic figures; consistent with the presence of a sarcoma without specific features.
